Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Selina Wang

2023-03-13

My meme

My meme is about in the dinner time, calling a sleepy cat for the dinner. The motivation of this meme is based on the animated character that I really like which is a black cat, and I was imagining about the daily activity of it and end up with the dinner idea. When I have made the decision about the content, I search for each part of my meme separately.

My dinner cat meme

library(magick)

# Create four parts

# First image with sleepy cat
image_1 = image_read("http://www.desktx.com/d/file/wallpaper/comic/20160921/8b991d519773832635b033041bab35e4.jpg") %>%
            image_scale("x200") %>%
            image_annotate(text = "Meow~~~", 
                           color = "#000000", 
                           size = 20, 
                           location = "+73+45")

# Second dialog
dialog_2 = image_blank(267, 200, "#065535") %>%
            image_annotate(text = "Dinner \nTime!",
                           color = "#FFFFFF",
                           size = 60, 
                           font = "Impact", 
                           gravity = "center")

# Third image with exciting cat
image_3 = image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTpiwFYV6CU1-aZ79Sa2gez9WU021feO3Z8XA&usqp=CAU") %>%
            image_scale("x200") %>%
            image_annotate(text = "Meow!", 
                           color = "#000000", 
                           size = 40, 
                           location = "+40+30")

# Fourth image of having the dinner
image_4 = image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ3W5uKnMVd192-JQcIq_8vyiNO48mJ7H9X1A&usqp=CAU") %>%
            image_scale("x200")


# Combine four parts
first_row = image_append(c(image_1, dialog_2))
second_row = image_append(c(image_3, image_4))
my_meme = image_append(c(first_row, second_row), stack = TRUE)
my_meme


# Save my meme as an image file
image_write(my_meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My animated GIF is about 12 months and some representative flowers for that month(searched from the internet). The motivation of my animation is because I know that I can get the names for each month in R using months.name, so I want to do some creation based on this information. Then, I Google about images relates to 12 months and end up with some flowers.

12 months flowers

library(magick)

# Create some useful data vectors
all_frames = c()
images_url = c("https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/carnations_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/primrose-pots-1188085_1920_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/AlmanacStaffArchive/daffodil-march_birth_flower-1920x1534px-pixabay_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/AlmanacStaffArchive/daisies-276112_1920_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/Linda%20Stonehill/lily-of-the-valley-updated-1280x960px_pixabay_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/rose-pink_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/water-lily_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/Linda%20Stonehill/gladiolus-updated-1920x1280px_pixabay_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/Linda%20Stonehill/asters-updated-1920x1275_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/flower-2469091_1920_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/The%20Editors/chrysanthemum-pink_full_width.jpg", 
               "https://www.almanac.com/sites/default/files/users/AlmanacStaffArchive/paperwhite_narcissus_december_birth_flower_2048x1536_credit_needed_wikimedia_full_width.jpg")
hex_colours = c("#fff2f4", "#f3685d", "#f8f675", "#f8f7a8", 
                         "#FFFFFF", "#f3aadd", "#f0aafb", "#fb5c5c",
                         "#b0a2fa", "#f5ac79", "#b8eda1", "#FFFFFF")
flower_names = c("Carnation", "Violet", "Daffodil", "Daisy", 
                 "Lily of the Valley", "Rose", "Larkspur", "Gladiolus", 
                 "Aster", "Marigold", "Chrysanthemum", "Narcissus")
flower_colour = c("#0b5394", "#6fa8dc", "#0b5394", "#6fa8dc", 
                           "#6fa8dc", "#6fa8dc", "#6fa8dc", "#6fa8dc", 
                           "#0b5394", "#6fa8dc", "#0b5394", "#6fa8dc")

                           
# Using a for loop to create all the frames
for (i in 1:12) {
  current_month = image_blank(400, 400, hex_colours[i]) %>% 
    image_annotate(text = month.name[i], 
                   color = "#000000", 
                   size = 70, 
                   gravity = "center", 
                   font = "Impact")
  
  flower_image = image_read(images_url[i]) %>% 
    image_scale("x400") %>% 
    image_annotate(text = flower_names[i], 
                   color = flower_colour[i], 
                   size = 35, 
                   location = "+20+10")
  
  temp_vector = c(current_month, flower_image)
  all_frames <- append(all_frames, temp_vector)
}

# Create the animation using the frame I created and the image_animate function
my_animation <- image_animate(all_frames, fps = 1)

# Save my animation as a .gif file
image_write(my_animation, "my_animation.gif")
